 {"id":"frankentorch-hc18","title":"tensor_unfold severs autograd; gather-then-scatter backward needed","description":"tensor_unfold at lib.rs:15083 extracts sliding windows. Each output element is a copy of an input element via a deterministic mapping (flat_out → in_flat). PyTorch's torch.Tensor.unfold IS differentiable.

Backward: scatter — grad_input[in_flat] += grad_output[flat_out] for each (flat_out, in_flat) pair the forward used. The mapping is deterministic given (dimension, size, step) and the input shape, so we can recompute it inside the backward closure.

Wrap in tensor_apply_function with this gather-then-scatter pattern.","notes":"Fixed in this commit. Wrapped tensor_unfold in tensor_apply_function with gather-then-scatter backward. The (flat_out -> in_flat) mapping is computed once in the outer body and captured by both forward (gather) and backward (scatter) closures so the same routing is used in both directions; overlapping windows (step < size) accumulate via += in the scatter. Added unfold_propagates_gradient_via_scatter regression test (x=[1,2,3,4], size=3, step=1 → 2 overlapping windows, grad_x = [1,2,2,1] under sum loss). ft-api lib tests: 1164.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-30T22:09:33.016426123Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-30T22:11:31.579946277Z","closed_at":"2026-04-30T22:11:31.577298295Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}

